    "describes": "Three income signals PDT can surface: (1) an ex-dividend date inside the lookahead window (forward-looking, works cold), (2) a dividend payment that just landed today, and (3) a dividend RAISE that must be DERIVED by comparing this period's recorded amount-per-share against the prior period — PDT exposes no explicit raise/cut flag. Calendar events also carry earnings dates.",
